The paper focuses on the impact of augmented reality head-mounted displays on users' movement behavior, which is related to human-computer interaction and ergonomics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also involves the use of multimedia technology, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). The study design and analysis involve spatial mapping and tag-along modes, which could be related to computer graphics and visualization (cs.GR). The paper also mentions the use of a dedicated trivial quiz task, which could involve information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques.
